{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CzBJt5keEexgHFh3RSrmLF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The init container `copy-cookie` copies the cookie from `rabbitmq-cookie-perpod` secret. The secret has different values for `rabbitmq-2` (`driftedcookie`) vs `rabbitmq-0` and `rabbitmq-1` (`supersecretcookie`).\n\nThe cookie is mounted read-only via an emptyDir volume (`erlang-cookie`), so changing the secret alone won't fix the running pod - we need to restart `rabbitmq-2` after fixing the secret so the init container re-runs with the correct cookie.\n\n**Fix plan:**\n1. Update `rabbitmq-2`'s cookie in the secret to match the others (encoding it in base64)\n2. Delete the `rabbitmq-2` pod to trigger a restart and let the init container copy the corrected cookie\n3. Once it comes back up, it should automatically rejoin the cluster since the configuration likely has cluster seeds defined\n\nLet me check the RabbitMQ configuration to confirm how the cluster is set up.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3077,"cache_read_input_tokens":31307,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3077},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5f2470b6-5c6e-4087-89ee-e362fe206b09","uuid":"c966a73c-8c02-4a32-a46d-113e3eacba30","request_id":"req_011CcMQGM4sraEKPKof5peqw"}
